<tool id="reformat_snpEff_for_SynTView" name="snp/indel convertor" version="0.0.1">
    <description>Convert a tabular snpEff file into a SynTView .snp and .indel files</description>
    <command>reformat_snpEff_for_SynTView.py 
    -p $inputptt 
    -s $inputsnp 
    #if $flaglog:
        -l $outputlog
    #end if
    -o output
    </command>
    <inputs>
        <param name="inputptt" type="data" format="tabular" label=".ptt file"/>
        <param name="inputsnp" type="data" format="tabular, vcf" label="snpEff output file"/>
        <param name="flaglog" type="boolean" checked="true" truevalue="yes" falsevalue="no" label="Optional log file"/>
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
        <data name="outputlog" format="txt" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string} log output">
            <filter>flaglog == 1</filter>
        </data>
        <data name="output_snp" format="tabular" from_work_dir="output.snp" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string} snp output"/>
        <data name="output_indel" format="tabular" from_work_dir="output.indel" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string} indel output"/>
    </outputs>
    <tests>
    </tests>
    <help>
    **What it does** 
    Convert a .txt tabular annotated variants file (generated by SnpEff) into a .snp and .indel custom files suited for SynTView integration, containing position, ref base, variant base (or length of indel), gene affected, strand, and protein effect. 
    </help>      
</tool>
